00024 /*
00025  * hgrow - Double the size of a hash table.
00026  * Allocate a new, 2x bigger array,
00027  * move everything from the old array to the new array,
00028  * then free the old array.
00029  */
00030 void hgrow()
00031 {
00032     ub4     newsize = (ub4)1<<(++pools_htab->logsize);
00033     ub4     newmask = newsize-1;
00034     ub4     i;
00035     HITEM   **old_hitem, **new_hitem;
00036 
00037     free(pools_hitem_row);
00038     pools_hitem_row = calloc(newsize, sizeof(ub4)) ;
00039 
00040     hitem_group->move = inithitem( newsize );
00041     
00042     old_hitem = hitem_group->usable;
00043     new_hitem = hitem_group->move;
00044    
00045     for(i=pools_htab->logsize; i--;){
00046         HITEM *this, *that, *new;
00047 
00048         if(!old_hitem[i]) continue;
00049         this = old_hitem[i]->next;
00050         
00051         while( this ){
00052             that = this;
00053             this = that->next;
00054 
00055             if(that->drl == 0) continue;  /* clear the empty drl  */
00056 
00057             new = new_hitem[(that->hval & newmask)];                
00058             that->next = new->next;
00059             new->next = that;
00060             pools_htab->count++;
00061         }
00062         hitem_group->bucket--;
00063     }
00064 
00065     freehitem(hitem_group->usable, pools_htab->logsize);
00066     
00067     hitem_group->usable = hitem_group->move;
00068     hitem_group->move = NULL;
00069     hitem_group->bucket = newsize;
00070     
00071     pools_htab->logsize = newsize; 
00072     pools_htab->mask = newmask;
00073 }
